div.div:
Each circle is represented as a hexagon, with all six sefirot. These sefirot are interacting with the outside sefirot that maintain relationship, but "radiate" around the border of the circle. They define the 4 directions that contain the 2d dynamics of our vivification.
However, using that same geometry, would it not place Malkut at the very centre.
If that is so, then what sits in the present Malkuth position?
Perhaps here is the mystery of the abyss... here is Da'at, the opening. It is what allows free choice!
Now these 6 inner sefirot are not all on a plane either. It would be something very similar to what is happening in the atom, with the electrons having a specific energy ordering, but the energy (represetned by e-) cannot be specifically identified. One cannot say something like "that electron identified by x, has moved from the s orbital to the p..."

div.span: Just as in the atom, it starts with the simple binary orbital, s. Then it reproduces that at the next level (called 2s), and adds the next 6, a new "ordital", named p, filling it with 8 electrons. That completes level 2, giving us 2 in the first orbital, and then 8 in the next for a total of 10. Then it starts again, 3s, 3p, and ... whoops now another level appears, named now 3d, but the process has become at level three, already complex enough to introduce some dissonance, and the progression is not quite smooth within these sublevels on 3. When that is done, we arrive at level 4, where it gets even more complex (thus dense... for dense is the description of this space), and the progression is even more erratic. This level does not complete, and consists of many strange atoms, until those at the furthest reach are unstable, some only lasting brief moments...
